div.div: Sayonara no Asa ni Yakusoku no Hana wo Kazarou

The people of Iorph live far away from the lands of men, weaving the happenings of each day into a fabric called Hibiol. They live for centuries while maintaining their youthful appearance. Maquia, an orphaned Iorph girl, lives her life in an oasis surrounded by friends, yet somehow feels “alone”. But the tranquil lives of the Iorph are shattered in an instant when the Mezarte army invades their territory on a dragon fleet, seeking the blood that grants the Iorph long life. Maquia manages to escape, but loses her friends and her home in the chaos. She then encounters an orphaned baby who is “alone”. Maquia raises this boy "Ariel", with the help of some new friends. But as the era changes, the bond between Maquia and Ariel changes too, amidst a backdrop of racial tensions between the Iorph and the Mezarte. This is a story of irreplaceable time, woven by two lonely people who can only find solace in each other.
(Source: Eleven Arts)
Comedy, Horror, Slice of Life, Supernatural

She can see dead people…she just chooses to ignore them. That’s Miko’s plan, anyway, but it doesn’t seem to be working for her in this love letter to the horror genre that will send shivers down your spine—and occasionally tickle your funny bone.
(Source: Funimation)
Tobioriru Chokuzen no Doukyuusei ni "XXX Shiyou!" to Teian Shitemita.

My first love, her name is Koga Gumomo.

She was so much more beautiful and mature than a typical high school student, which attracted a great deal of jealousy and dislike. So much so that she was on the verge of jumping off the rooftop because of all the bullying she received.

So, what can I do to help?

"Why not have s*x with me!"
"............, you pervert! ...... (yuck!)"
"Maybe so! But are you sure? If you die here, your last memory will be the confession of some pervert you don't even know! It would ruin the mood!"
"............, what have you done! You pervert!"
"I have my reasons. Because I love you more than anything in the world! Let's get married!"
"What, ehhhh~~~............?"

I will yell out my love until I die, if it will make a place for you in this world!

The most stupid and straightforward protagonist in the history of romantic comedies and the cool, sullen JK will hook up for a romantic comedy with a sugar content of 100%!

(Source: Dengeki Bunko, translated)
Takane-san, Kimi no Koto Sukirashii yo

"I heard that Takamine-san likes you."
The head of the school discipline committee, Kengo Mashima, heard a rumor from an unknown source...... It turned out that the source was none other than Takamine-san herself, who wanted Mashima-kun to show more interest in her! But the overly serious Mashima-kun didn't get the hint: ......
"Saki Takamine, I heard you have a crush on me?"
"Why are you asking me for? ......!"
Actually, Mashima-kun liked Takamine-san, too. The first time you see these two, you'll be writhing in frustration at their innocent denseness!
(Source: Gagaga Bunko, translated)
